  <h2>Standard vs HA Deployment</h2>
  <p>
    <strong>Standard mode</strong> deploys a single controller Compute Engine instance with a zonal Cloud SQL
    instance. Suitable for non-critical workloads.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>HA mode</strong> deploys two controller instances across separate zones, a regional (HA) Cloud SQL
    instance with automatic failover, and a regional Managed Instance Group for agents spread across all zones in
    the selected region.
  </p>

  <h2>Prerequisites</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Terraform 1.6 or later</li>
    <li>Google Cloud SDK (<code>gcloud</code>) installed and authenticated</li>
    <li>A GCP project with billing enabled</li>
    <li>A service account with <strong>Editor</strong> role or the following granular roles: Compute Admin, Cloud SQL Admin, Filestore Editor, Service Account User, IAP-secured Tunnel User</li>
    <li>Application Default Credentials configured: <code>gcloud auth application-default login</code></li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Enable Required APIs</h2>
  <pre><code>gcloud services enable \
  compute.googleapis.com \
  sqladmin.googleapis.com \
  file.googleapis.com \
  servicenetworking.googleapis.com \
  iap.googleapis.com \
  --project=my-project-id</code></pre>

  <h2>Quick Start</h2>
  <pre><code># 1. Navigate to the GCP Terraform directory
cd deploy/terraform/gcp

# 2. Copy and configure variables
cp terraform.tfvars.example terraform.tfvars
$EDITOR terraform.tfvars</code></pre>

  <pre><code># terraform.tfvars
project_id           = "my-project-id"
region               = "us-central1"
zone                 = "us-central1-a"
encodeswarmr_version = "1.2.0"

# Controller
controller_machine_type = "n2-standard-2"

# Agents
agent_machine_type   = "c2-standard-8"
agent_min_replicas   = 1
agent_max_replicas   = 10

# Cloud SQL
db_tier              = "db-g1-small"
db_user              = "encodeswarmr"
db_password          = "changeme"

# Filestore
filestore_tier       = "STANDARD"
filestore_capacity_gb = 1024</code></pre>

  <pre><code># 3. Initialise and apply
terraform init
terraform plan
terraform apply</code></pre>

  <h2>Enabling HA</h2>
  <pre><code># terraform.tfvars additions for HA
ha_enabled           = true
controller_count     = 2
db_availability_type = "REGIONAL"   # Cloud SQL HA
agent_zones          = ["us-central1-a", "us-central1-b", "us-central1-c"]</code></pre>

  <pre><code>terraform apply -var="ha_enabled=true"</code></pre>

  <h2>Remote State on GCS</h2>
  <pre><code># Create a GCS bucket for state
gsutil mb -p my-project-id -l us-central1 gs://my-tfstate-bucket
gsutil versioning set on gs://my-tfstate-bucket</code></pre>

  <pre><code># backend.tf
terraform &#123;
  backend "gcs" &#123;
    bucket = "my-tfstate-bucket"
    prefix = "encodeswarmr/gcp"
  &#125;
&#125;</code></pre>

  <h2>SSH Access via IAP</h2>
  <p>Instances have no external IP addresses. Use Identity-Aware Proxy (IAP) tunnelling for SSH access:</p>
  <pre><code># SSH to the controller via IAP
gcloud compute ssh encodeswarmr-controller-01 \
  --tunnel-through-iap \
  --project=my-project-id \
  --zone=us-central1-a

# Port-forward the web UI to localhost for initial configuration
gcloud compute start-iap-tunnel encodeswarmr-controller-01 8080 \
  --local-host-port=localhost:8080 \
  --zone=us-central1-a \
  --project=my-project-id</code></pre>

